# Contributing to Awesome Hugging Face Models

Thank you for your interest in contributing to this curated list of Hugging Face models! Your contributions help make this resource more valuable for the entire ML community.

## 🚀 Quick Start

1. **Fork** the repository
2. **Create** a new branch for your contribution
3. **Add** your model(s) following our format
4. **Submit** a pull request with a clear description

## 📋 How to Contribute

### Adding a New Model

To add a model to the list, please ensure it meets our [inclusion criteria](#inclusion-criteria) and follow this format:

```markdown
| [model-creator/model-name](https://huggingface.co/model-creator/model-name) | Brief description of the model's purpose and capabilities | Additional info (size, languages, etc.) | [🚀 Demo](https://huggingface.co/model-creator/model-name) |
```

**Example:**
```markdown
| [microsoft/DialoGPT-large](https://huggingface.co/microsoft/DialoGPT-large) | Conversational AI model fine-tuned on Reddit conversations | 345M | [🚀 Demo](https://huggingface.co/microsoft/DialoGPT-large) |
```

### Types of Contributions We Welcome

- ✅ **New model additions** - High-quality, well-documented models
- ✅ **Model updates** - Performance improvements, new versions
- ✅ **Broken link fixes** - Dead links or outdated information
- ✅ **Documentation improvements** - Better descriptions, examples
- ✅ **Benchmark updates** - New performance metrics and comparisons
- ✅ **Category suggestions** - New task categories or reorganization
- ✅ **Usage examples** - Code snippets and tutorials

## 📝 Inclusion Criteria

For a model to be included in this list, it should meet **at least 3 of the following criteria**:

### Quality & Performance
- [ ] Achieves state-of-the-art or competitive performance on standard benchmarks
- [ ] Has been cited in academic papers or widely adopted in industry
- [ ] Demonstrates clear improvements over existing alternatives

### Documentation & Usability
- [ ] Has comprehensive documentation on Hugging Face Hub
- [ ] Includes clear usage examples and model card
- [ ] Is actively maintained or comes from a reputable organization

### Community Impact
- [ ] Has significant community adoption (downloads, likes, usage)
- [ ] Addresses an important use case or fills a gap in available models
- [ ] Is recommended by ML practitioners or researchers

### Technical Requirements
- [ ] Is publicly available on Hugging Face Hub
- [ ] Has a clear license for usage
- [ ] Works with the Transformers library or other standard frameworks

## 🎯 Contribution Guidelines

### Model Descriptions
- Keep descriptions **concise but informative** (1-2 sentences)
- Focus on **what the model does** and **what makes it special**
- Mention key features like multilingual support, fine-tuning dataset, or novel architecture
- Use consistent terminology across similar models

### Links and Demos
- **Always link directly to the Hugging Face model page**
- Verify that demo links work before submitting
- If no interactive demo exists, link to the model card instead
- Use the 🚀 emoji for demo links consistently

### Categories and Organization
- Place models in the **most appropriate category**
- If unsure, suggest a new category in your PR description
- Maintain **alphabetical order** within categories when possible
- Keep table formatting consistent

### Code Examples
- Use **working, tested code snippets**
- Include necessary imports and dependencies
- Keep examples **simple and focused**
- Follow Python best practices and PEP 8 style

## 🔍 Before Submitting

Please check the following before submitting your contribution:

- [ ] **No duplicates** - Model isn't already listed
- [ ] **Working links** - All URLs are accessible and correct
- [ ] **Proper formatting** - Tables and markdown syntax are correct
- [ ] **Spell check** - No typos in descriptions or model names
- [ ] **Category fit** - Model is in the appropriate section
- [ ] **License check** - Model has appropriate licensing for inclusion

## 📐 Pull Request Process

1. **Create a descriptive title**
   ```
   Add [model-name] for [task-type]
   Fix broken link for [model-name]
   Update benchmark results for [category]
   ```

2. **Provide context in the description**
   - Why is this model valuable?
   - What makes it different from existing options?
   - Any relevant performance metrics or benchmarks?

3. **Reference related issues** (if applicable)
   ```
   Closes #123
   Addresses #456
   ```

4. **Be patient and responsive**
   - Maintainers will review your PR as soon as possible
   - Be open to feedback and suggestions
   - Make requested changes promptly

## 🚫 What We Don't Accept

- **Proprietary or closed-source models** not available on Hugging Face
- **Models with unclear licensing** or usage restrictions
- **Deprecated or unmaintained models** (unless historically significant)
- **Models designed for harmful purposes** (hate speech, misinformation, etc.)
- **Duplicate entries** of models already listed
- **Self-promotion without merit** - models must meet quality standards
- **Incomplete information** - missing descriptions, broken links, etc.

## 🏷️ Model Categories

If your model doesn't fit existing categories, suggest a new one! We're open to:
- New task types as they emerge
- Splitting large categories for better organization
- Creating specialized subcategories
- Cross-category tags for models that serve multiple purposes

### Current Categories
- **Natural Language Processing**: LLMs, classification, NER, QA, summarization, translation, code generation
- **Computer Vision**: Classification, detection, segmentation, generation, OCR
- **Audio Processing**: Speech recognition, TTS, classification, generation
- **Multimodal**: Vision-language, audio-text models

## ⚡ Quick Tips

- **Start small** - Add one model first to get familiar with the process
- **Check recent PRs** - See what others have contributed recently
- **Ask questions** - Open an issue if you're unsure about anything
- **Be specific** - Include version numbers, dataset names, and performance metrics when relevant
- **Stay updated** - Follow the repository to see new contributions and updates

## 🎉 Recognition

Contributors are recognized in several ways:
- Listed in repository contributors
- Mentioned in release notes for significant contributions
- Community recognition for high-quality additions

## 📞 Getting Help

If you need assistance:

1. **Check existing issues** - Your question might already be answered
2. **Open a new issue** - For questions about contribution guidelines
3. **Start a discussion** - For broader topics or suggestions
4. **Review the README** - For formatting examples and model categories

## 📊 Contribution Examples

### Adding a New Model
```markdown
### Before (in appropriate category table):
| Model | Description | Details | Demo |

### Add:
| [facebook/wav2vec2-large-960h](https://huggingface.co/facebook/wav2vec2-large-960h) | Self-supervised speech recognition model trained on 960 hours of LibriSpeech | English, 317M params | [🚀 Demo](https://huggingface.co/facebook/wav2vec2-large-960h) |
```

### Updating Model Information
```markdown
### Before:
| [model-name](link) | Old description | Outdated info | [🚀 Demo](link) |

### After:
| [model-name](link) | Updated description with new capabilities | Current version info | [🚀 Demo](working-link) |
```

### Adding a New Category
```markdown
## 🧬 Bioinformatics

| Model | Description | Specialization | Demo |
|-------|-------------|----------------|------|
| [model-example](link) | Description | Details | [🚀 Demo](link) |
```

## 🔄 Keeping Content Current

Help us maintain quality by:
- Reporting outdated model information
- Suggesting when models should be removed or deprecated
- Adding new benchmark results as they become available
- Updating model descriptions when new capabilities are added

Thank you for contributing to the awesome Hugging Face models community! 🤗

---

**Questions?** Feel free to open an issue or start a discussion.

**Found a bug?** Please report it so we can fix it quickly.

**Have an idea?** We'd love to hear your suggestions for improving this resource!

